The City of Cape Town has outlined a 10-point plan that it believes could spell the end of rolling blackouts. The plan involves the establishment of a Power Crisis Unit in National Treasury. eNCA speaks to Cape Town Mayor Geordin Hill-Lewis for more. Courtesy #DStv403  CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town has outlined a 10-point plan that it believes could spell the end of rolling blackouts. The plan involves the establishment of a Power Crisis Unit in the National Treasury. READ: Cape Town avoids Stage 6 blackouts This would enable regulatory decisions and cut the red tape on the establishment of natural gas imports, among other things. The city says the electricity crisis can only be solved if President Cyril Ramaphosa acts decisively and makes bold decisions. Watch the video above for more details. 